Introduction

DAWN is a South Korean rapper, songwriter, and composer. He is a former member of PENTAGON and the co-ed group Triple H.

He debuted with PENTAGON on October 10, 2016, with the mini-album PENTAGON. In 2017, he joined Triple H alongside Hui and Hyuna, debuting with the EP 199X on May 1. After confirming his relationship with Hyuna in August 2018, Cube Entertainment announced his absence from PENTAGON's Thumbs Up! promotions. On November 14, 2018, his departure from Cube and PENTAGON was officially confirmed.

DAWN signed with P Nation in January 2019 and made his solo debut on November 5 with the digital single Money. He remained under the label until August 2022, shortly before his breakup with Hyuna in November. In January 2023, he signed with hip-hop label AT AREA, releasing Dear My Light on April 13 as his first single under the company.

On October 12, 2023, DAWN revealed that he had enlisted quietly as a public service worker. He is expected to complete his military service on July 11, 2025.
